{
  "id": 5176753681203200,
  "name": "Refine border-radius shadow edge computation for high border-radius",
  "summary": "This improvement ensures that shadows and clip boundaries on near-circular elements (where border-radius is close to 50%) precisely match the visual contour of the curved edge.\n\nThis produces a more consistent rendering of complex rounded shapes, eliminating visual discrepancies for high radius values. The border-radius adjustment factor, which ensures corners appear sharp for small radii, is now progressively dampened as the radius value approaches 50%.\n\nThis also applies to non-round contours (using corner-shape), which now use the same radius adjustment mechanism.",
